FBIS4-48111 "drafr092_c_94007" FBIS-AFR-94-092 Daily Report 12 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA UK Military Instructors To Arrive in June UK Military Instructors To Arrive in June MB1205082694 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 0600 GMT 12 May 94 MB1205082694 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network Afrikaans BFN [Text] Britain is to send a 31-member military team to South Africa next month to assist in the integration of the country's new National Defense Force. British Defense Minister Malcolm Rifkind said in London the team will supervise training in the Army, Air Force, the Navy and the Medical Corps. Nine of the instructors will stay on for two years and the rest for six months.
